  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This is an enhancement request to add a command line option to specify the truffle config file to be used on compilation.\r\n\r\nThe use case I have is I'm using the Gnosis MultiSigWallet which requires Solidity `0.4.15` while the other contracts in my app are using `0.5.11` as I need ABIEncoderV2. At the moment I put the MultiSigWallet contract in a different folder and manually modify my `truffle-config.js` file to specify the compiler version to use for the folder I want to compile.\r\n\r\nIdeally, I'd like to have two truffle config files and just use a command line option to specify which config file to use when compiling. That means in a continuous integration build, two truffle compile commands would be run.\r\n",
